msgid "make_face()"
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_design.rst:98
msgid ""
"*This command creates a 2D face from the closed profile. The offset "
"operation ensures that the profile is closed, allowing the creation of a "
"solid face from the boundary defined.*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_design.rst:100
msgid "mirror(about=Plane.YZ)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_design.rst:101
msgid ""
"*This mirrors the entire face about the YZ plane (which runs along the "
"center of the sketch), creating a symmetrical counterpart of the face. The "
"mirrored geometry will complete the final shape.*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_design.rst:104
msgid "Step 5. Use Extrusion for Prismatic Features"
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_design.rst:105
msgid ""
"For solid or prismatic shapes, extrude the 2D profiles along the necessary "
"axis. You can also combine multiple extrusions by intersecting or unionizing"
" them to form complex shapes. Use the resulting geometry as sub-parts if "
"needed."
msgstr ""

