msgid "*This code creates a hole in a specific face of the bracket part.*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_design.rst:201
msgid "with Locations(bracket.faces().sort_by(Axis.X)[-1]):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_design.rst:202
msgid "*This context sets a location(s) for subsequent operations.*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_design.rst:204
#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_design.rst:233
msgid "bracket.faces() *retrieves all the faces of the bracket part.*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_design.rst:205
msgid ""
"sort_by(Axis.X) *sorts these faces based on their position along the X-axis "
"(from one side of the bracket to the other).*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_design.rst:207
msgid ""
"[-1] *selects the last face in this sorted list, which would be the face "
"farthest along the X-axis, the extreme right side of the part.*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_design.rst:209
msgid ""
"Locations() *creates a new local context or coordinate system at the "
"selected face, effectively setting this face as the working location for any"
" subsequent operations inside the with block.*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_design.rst:213
msgid "Hole(hole_diameter / 2)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_design.rst:214
msgid ""
"*This creates a hole in the selected face. The radius of the hole is "
"specified as hole_diameter / 2. The hole is placed at the origin of the "
"selected face, based on the local coordinate system created by Locations(). "
"As the depth of the hole is not provided it is assumed to go entirely "
"through the part.*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_design.rst:219
msgid ""
"*Next the slot needs to be created in the bracket with will be done by "
"sketching a slot on the front of the bracket and extruding the sketch "
"through the part.*"
msgstr ""

